Ingredients.2: 1  zucchini, quartered lengthwise and cut into 1/2-inch pieces

Ingredients.4: 1 salt and ground black pepper to taste

Directions.1: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil.

Directions.2: Drizzle 2 tablespoons olive oil onto the prepared baking sheet; place zucchini slices in the oil. Drizzle 3 more tablespoons olive oil over zucchini slices; season with salt and black pepper. Toss coated zucchini slices with 1 cup bread crumbs.

Directions.3: Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes. Toss zucchini slices with remaining 1 cup bread crumbs. Return to oven and bake until zucchini is soft and bread crumbs are lightly browned, 15 to 20 minutes.
